commit.message:
Fix ordering of combo boxes (#53)

When iterating over a std::map, the order is not guaranteed. In this case,
it was ordering the items by alphabetic order of name, instead of the order
in the xml files. This was causing the initially selected item to not match
the actual value in some cases. Fix this by using a std::vector of std::pairs.

verification.payload:
tree 2da56324be237e00babb56419bd60fc24957abcf
parent 676f9813c89a67f4672137970b5e2c180501d98e
author Scott Moreau <oreaus@gmail.com> 1677856035 -0700
committer GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1677856035 -0700

Fix ordering of combo boxes (#53)

When iterating over a std::map, the order is not guaranteed. In this case,
it was ordering the items by alphabetic order of name, instead of the order
in the xml files. This was causing the initially selected item to not match
the actual value in some cases. Fix this by using a std::vector of std::pairs.

commit.message:
Present window when wcm is run again (#50)

When wcm is run while it is already running, nothing happened because
it is single instance. Calling GtkWindow.present() gives wayfire an
indication to raise the window, so it doesn't seem broken.

verification.payload:
tree f801d2482854e843ca7f24c63008446d8a8105a9
parent aa9ff0c4f8e3dbbd57c651edf01040c6e9c27e02

committer GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1677521684 -0700

Present window when wcm is run again (#50)

When wcm is run while it is already running, nothing happened because
it is single instance. Calling GtkWindow.present() gives wayfire an
indication to raise the window, so it doesn't seem broken.
